def get_optimzied_weight(cov):
    w=tuple([1/(len(cov.columns)) for i in cov.columns])
    bnds=tuple([(None,0.5) for i in cov.columns])
    #avg=port.mean().to_numpy()
    #cov=port.cov().to_numpy()
    #miu=np.matmul(np.array([1/len(port.columns) for i in port.columns]),avg)
    def weight_constrain(w):
        return np.matmul(w,np.ones(len(w)))-1
#     def return_constrain(w):
#         return np.matmul(w,avg)-miu
    def variance(weight):
        return np.matmul(np.matmul(weight,cov),weight)
    cons = [{'type': 'eq', 'fun': weight_constrain}]
    return minimize(variance,w,constraints=cons,bounds=bnds)
def get_sharp(returns,rf):
    rf=rf[returns.index[0]:]
    returns=returns.T.to_numpy()[0]
    excess_return=returns-rf
    return (np.mean(excess_return)/np.std(excess_return))*np.sqrt(12),np.mean(returns)*12,np.std(returns)*12
